This paper deals with software quality metrics and their relationship with software usage, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also uses Bayesian Network and Random Forest models, which are commonly used in programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The analysis of NPM packages involves code complexity measures, which is related to software security (cs.CR) and software infrastructure (cs.SI).
